Great question — and good instinct.

Storing the whole document in the snapshot is usually the wiser move for production:
	•	Pros: future‑proof (if new tracked fields are added later, you can compute deltas without re‑baselining), great for audits/replay/debugging, simpler export/BI.
	•	Cons: more storage/read I/O. You can mitigate with lifecycle/retention (e.g., keep last N versions or 90 days).

If storage is acceptable (it usually is on Blob), I recommend full‑doc snapshots + compare only the tracked paths at runtime.

